634
00:42:33,783 --> 00:42:35,285
No way,

635
00:42:35,493 --> 00:42:37,871
I don't need to pay for women.

636
00:42:38,538 --> 00:42:39,664
GRANDMA WONG: Hmm.

637
00:42:41,833 --> 00:42:43,126
Was she pretty?

638
00:42:44,627 --> 00:42:46,337
Yan Yan. She's really pretty.

639
00:42:47,005 --> 00:42:48,423
(CHUCKLING)

640
00:42:50,675 --> 00:42:52,677
(MELLOW SONG PLAYING IN MANDARIN)

641
00:42:54,721 --> 00:42:55,805
(SCOFFS)

642
00:42:58,391 --> 00:42:59,434
(GRUNTS)

643
00:42:59,517 --> 00:43:01,019
Hmm? Wait, that's it?

644
00:43:01,102 --> 00:43:03,688
I need to take my bath.

645
00:43:04,355 --> 00:43:08,026
- Then we can watch the next one.
- (CHUCKLES)

646
00:43:08,109 --> 00:43:11,488
No starting without me!

647
00:43:11,571 --> 00:43:13,740
(IN ENGLISH) Okay. (CHUCKLES)

648
00:43:17,285 --> 00:43:18,495
(SLURPING)

649
00:43:19,037 --> 00:43:20,246
(EXHALES)

650
00:43:22,832 --> 00:43:24,542
- (EXHALES)
- (TAP RUNNING)

651
00:43:25,585 --> 00:43:27,420
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

652
00:43:29,339 --> 00:43:31,257
(IN MANDARIN) Hello.

653
00:43:31,341 --> 00:43:34,094
You saw the beta?

654
00:43:34,177 --> 00:43:38,556
How come I can't log in?

655
00:43:38,807 --> 00:43:40,016
Just a second.

656
00:43:50,777 --> 00:43:52,946
Gong, can you hear me?

657
00:43:53,029 --> 00:43:55,532
I'm not sure when I'll be back.

658
00:43:57,826 --> 00:43:59,244
(GRUNTING)

659
00:44:01,413 --> 00:44:02,622
Whoo!

660
00:44:08,628 --> 00:44:10,755
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

661
00:44:20,181 --> 00:44:21,808
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

662
00:44:24,978 --> 00:44:27,063
(OBJECTS CONTINUE CLATTERING)

663
00:44:39,075 --> 00:44:40,410
(PANTING)

664
00:44:40,493 --> 00:44:41,703
(GRUNTING)

665
00:44:47,459 --> 00:44:48,835
MAN: Little Handsome!

666
00:44:51,838 --> 00:44:53,089
Little Handsome!

667
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:55,049
(GRUNTS)

668
00:44:58,178 --> 00:44:59,596
(GRUNTING)

669
00:45:08,563 --> 00:45:09,981
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

670
00:45:33,505 --> 00:45:35,340
(OBJECTS RUSTLING)

671
00:45:44,682 --> 00:45:46,351
- (GRANDMA WONG GRUNTS)
- (GROANS)

672
00:45:46,434 --> 00:45:47,602
MAN: What the hell.

673
00:45:47,852 --> 00:45:49,604
(BOTH GRUNTING)

674
00:45:53,441 --> 00:45:54,901
- Grandma Wong!
- (GROANS)

675
00:45:54,984 --> 00:45:56,653
- Where's the money?
- Get away from me!

676
00:45:56,736 --> 00:45:57,737
Where's the money?

677
00:45:58,613 --> 00:45:59,739
Tell me!

678
00:46:02,575 --> 00:46:03,576
Tell me!

679
00:46:04,160 --> 00:46:05,203
Where is the money?

680
00:46:05,286 --> 00:46:06,287
Grandma Wong!

681
00:46:06,371 --> 00:46:08,039
Tell me! Where is the money?

682
00:46:08,123 --> 00:46:09,124
Where is the money?

683
00:46:10,834 --> 00:46:12,544
(GROANING)

684
00:46:15,505 --> 00:46:17,132
(GRUNTING)

685
00:46:19,217 --> 00:46:20,510
(GRANDMA WONG SCREAMS)

686
00:46:22,512 --> 00:46:23,555
(GRUNTS)

687
00:46:25,390 --> 00:46:26,391
(THUD)

688
00:47:01,885 --> 00:47:03,386
GRANDMA WONG: What do we do now?

689
00:47:06,222 --> 00:47:07,307
Big Pong!

690
00:47:08,099 --> 00:47:09,225
Big Pong!

691
00:47:09,851 --> 00:47:12,353
What do we do?
Should we move him?

692
00:47:13,855 --> 00:47:15,440
- I don't know.
- Huh?

693
00:47:16,483 --> 00:47:18,777
You haven't done this before?

694
00:47:20,195 --> 00:47:22,155
You... you...

695
00:47:22,238 --> 00:47:25,533
Maybe you should call someone?

696
00:47:25,617 --> 00:47:27,452
(BIG PONG BREATHING SHAKILY)

697
00:47:28,328 --> 00:47:29,329
No?

698
00:47:31,331 --> 00:47:32,373
Okay.

699
00:47:34,250 --> 00:47:35,585
Forget it.

700
00:47:44,677 --> 00:47:46,513
(STRAINING)

701
00:47:48,973 --> 00:47:51,976
Hey, help me!

702
00:47:52,185 --> 00:47:53,812
- Come here and help!
- Hmm?

703
00:48:26,511 --> 00:48:27,720
(BIG PONG GRUNTS)

704
00:48:32,517 --> 00:48:33,935
(SCRAPING)

705
00:48:37,814 --> 00:48:38,898
(GRUNTING)

706
00:48:48,700 --> 00:48:50,535
(PANTING)

707
00:48:54,414 --> 00:48:56,249
- (GRUNTING)
- (THUDDING)

708
00:49:04,549 --> 00:49:06,551
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

709
00:49:11,848 --> 00:49:13,850
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

710
00:49:31,409 --> 00:49:33,369
It's not your fault.

711
00:49:33,453 --> 00:49:35,747
I was almost killed.

712
00:49:40,460 --> 00:49:43,338
We should tell Sister Fong.

713
00:49:44,047 --> 00:49:45,381
Ok.

714
00:49:46,508 --> 00:49:47,967
Why?

715
00:49:50,095 --> 00:49:51,805
She'll find out anyway.

716
00:49:51,888 --> 00:49:53,765
She always finds out.

717
00:49:53,848 --> 00:49:56,392
Hmm. We should tell her

718
00:49:56,476 --> 00:49:58,019
to give you a raise.

719
00:49:58,103 --> 00:50:00,730
She won't be happy.

720
00:50:00,939 --> 00:50:03,525
We shouldn't create direct
conflict with the Red Dragon.

721
00:50:04,567 --> 00:50:06,361
Well, we won't tell her then.

722
00:50:07,654 --> 00:50:10,407
(SIGHS) This can't be...

723
00:50:10,490 --> 00:50:12,992
I...

724
00:50:13,076 --> 00:50:14,369
I don't know...

725
00:50:14,452 --> 00:50:16,538
This really can't be.

726
00:50:16,788 --> 00:50:18,832
You saved my life.

727
00:50:21,334 --> 00:50:22,419
Don't worry.

728
00:50:22,502 --> 00:50:24,212
You're a good boy.

729
00:50:24,587 --> 00:50:28,591
Let's act like nothing happened.

730
00:50:32,095 --> 00:50:34,472
WOMAN: (IN ENGLISH) Pong,
would you like some more water?

731
00:50:34,556 --> 00:50:36,975
- Huh? Thank you.
- WOMAN: Okay.

732
00:50:37,058 --> 00:50:39,769
So, how did, uh,
how did you two meet?

733
00:50:39,853 --> 00:50:41,271
Are you Grandma's boyfriend?

734
00:50:41,354 --> 00:50:42,939
PETER: Grandma has a boyfriend?

735
00:50:43,022 --> 00:50:45,233
MAN: Guys.
Can you let us talk, please?

736
00:50:45,316 --> 00:50:46,484
DAVID: Grandma, are you okay?

737
00:50:46,568 --> 00:50:49,154
WOMAN: How long have you been
in the States?

738
00:50:49,237 --> 00:50:51,990
MAN: Uh, is your ankle
bothering you again, Ma?

739
00:50:52,073 --> 00:50:53,616
(IN MANDARIN) I'm fine.

740
00:50:53,700 --> 00:50:55,869
PETER: (IN ENGLISH)
Wait. What did she say?

741
00:50:55,952 --> 00:50:58,246
DAVID: She says you should
learn Chinese, <i>bendan.</i>

742
00:50:58,329 --> 00:50:59,748
MAN: Hey.
DAVID: Big Pong likes Beyoncé.

743
00:50:59,831 --> 00:51:01,249
PETER: Who doesn't like Bey?

744
00:51:01,332 --> 00:51:03,251
- DAVID: I don't.
- She's a little fake.

745
00:51:03,334 --> 00:51:04,961
Ma, I, uh... I hear

746
00:51:05,044 --> 00:51:08,006
you and Big Pong took care of that guy.

747
00:51:08,089 --> 00:51:09,299
How did you do it?

748
00:51:10,133 --> 00:51:11,134
GRANDMA WONG: Huh?

749
00:51:11,217 --> 00:51:14,471
I... I said I heard that
you and Big Pong's dad

750
00:51:14,554 --> 00:51:16,973
were old friends in Jiangsu.
How did you meet?

751
00:51:19,017 --> 00:51:21,019
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

752
00:51:21,686 --> 00:51:23,521
(DISTANT BEEPING)

753
00:51:33,948 --> 00:51:35,450
(HORN BLARES IN DISTANCE)

754
00:51:40,080 --> 00:51:41,289
(BEEPING STOPS)

755
00:51:41,372 --> 00:51:43,208
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

756
00:51:59,015 --> 00:52:00,517
(SIGHS)

757
00:52:02,602 --> 00:52:03,812
(LIGHTER CLOSES)

758
00:52:28,920 --> 00:52:30,088
(IN MANDARIN) Big Pong.

